<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,402,823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,402,427]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western 
<collectingCountry box="[416,506,402,427]" name="Lesotho" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Lesotho</collectingCountry>
and adjacent southeastern Free State and Eastern Cape provinces, 
<collectingCountry box="[1289,1436,402,427]" name="South Africa" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" box="[158,402,439,463]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2014 a) Afroedura halli (Hewitt, 1935). In: Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. (Eds.), Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata, 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, pp. 91 - 92." type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Bates &amp; Bauer 
<number box="[332,390,439,463]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2014.0">2014</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[425,494,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1165,1187]" captionTargetBox="[181,1379,205,1164]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[172,1393,177,1165]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map of southern Africa showing the approximate distributional ranges of previously described species of Afroedura. Red dots represent localities sampled for the genetic portion of the study. Ranges based on Branch (1998) and Bates et al. (2014) as well as unpublished data. Taxon names follow the conclusions of this paper. Area demarcated by a dashed line is presented in more detail in Figure 6." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250499/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number box="[477,494,439,463]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,402,823]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,474,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[944,1070,474,499]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="karroica">
<emphasis box="[944,1070,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. karroica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge" box="[1140,1322,474,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Loveridge, A. (1947) Revision of the African lizards of the Family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 98, 1 - 469, pls. 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1947">
Loveridge 
<number box="[1262,1322,475,499]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wermuth" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Wermuth, H. (1965) Liste der rezenten Amphibien und Reptilien, Gekkonidae, Pygopodidae, Xantusiidae. Das Tierreich, 80, xxii + 246 pp." type="book" year="1965">
Wermuth 
<number box="[151,210,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1965.0">1965</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Branch 
<emphasis box="[310,359,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[373,432,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1988.0">1988</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge" box="[444,578,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (1991) Checklist of Gekkonid lizards. Smithsonian Herpetological Information Service, 85, 1 - 35. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 23317515.85.1" type="journal article" year="1991">Kluge 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge" box="[590,647,511,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (1993) Checklist of Gekkonid Lizards. International Gecko Society, San Diego, 245 pp." type="book" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
) but was elevated to specific status by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" box="[1087,1233,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Bates, M. F. (1996) In search of the elusive flat geckos of the eastern Free State. Culna 51, 13 - 15." type="journal article" year="1996">
Bates (
<number box="[1165,1225,510,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, although without substantial discussion, and some later authors, especially outside of 
<collectingCountry box="[945,1095,546,571]" name="South Africa" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, have continued to include it within 
<taxonomicName box="[234,366,582,607]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="karroica">
<emphasis box="[234,366,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. karroica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge" box="[447,587,582,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Kluge, A. G. (2001) Gekkotan lizard taxonomy. Hamadryad, 26, 1 - 209." type="journal article" year="2001">
Kluge 
<number box="[527,587,583,607]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). One subspecies, 
<taxonomicName box="[809,960,582,607]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="karroica" subSpecies="wilmoti">
<emphasis box="[809,960,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. k. wilmoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has been variously recognized as valid (
<bibRefCitation author="FitzSimons" box="[158,353,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="FitzSimons, V. F. (1943) The lizards of South Africa. Memoirs of the Transvaal Museum, 1, i - xv + 1 - 528, + 24 pls + map." type="journal article" year="1943">
FitzSimons 
<number box="[296,353,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) or not (
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge" box="[453,637,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Loveridge, A. (1947) Revision of the African lizards of the Family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 98, 1 - 469, pls. 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1947">
Loveridge 
<number box="[578,637,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1947.0">1947</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Branch" box="[651,800,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Branch, W. R. (1981) An annotated checklist of the lizards of the Cape Province, South Africa. Annals of the Cape Provincial Museums (Natural History), 13, 141 - 167." type="journal article" year="1981">
Branch 
<number box="[740,800,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Its status is under review (
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" box="[1120,1372,618,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Bates, M. F. &amp; Branch, W. R. (1998) Taxonomy and distribution of the Afroedura nivaria and A. karroica complexes (Sauria: Gekkonidae). Herpetological Association of Africa, Fifth Symposium, University of Stellenbosch, 14 - 16 September 1998, Programme and Abstracts. [2 unnumbered pages]" type="book chapter" year="1998">
Bates &amp; Branch 
<number box="[1312,1372,619,643]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Our sampling included a single specimen resembling 
<taxonomicName box="[702,784,654,679]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="halli">
<emphasis box="[702,784,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. halli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was deeply divergent from all other samples (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1418,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1708,1730]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,490,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[147,1432,481,1677]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood phylogram of Afroedura relationships derived from two genes (ND 2, RAG 1). Support values are presented as maximum likelihood bootstraps (MLBS) / Bayesian posterior probabilities (BPP) / parsimony bootstraps (PBS). Only most closely related outgroup taxa are shown. Images (top to bottom) of representative Afroedura species groups: A. hawequensis, A. pondolia, A. karroica, A. loveridgei, A. haackei, A. marleyi, A. granitica sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/250496/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1418,655,679]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), supporting the findings of 
<bibRefCitation author="Makhubo" box="[450,641,690,715]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" refString="Makhubo, B. G. (2013) Phylogenetic and Morphological Analysis of the Afroedura nivaria (Reptilia: Gekkonidae) Species Complex in South Africa. Unpublished M. Sc. Thesis, University of Stellenbosch, xiii + 106 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Makhubo (
<number box="[572,633,691,715]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2013.0">2013</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who found multiple divergent clades within the species. Although the distinctiveness of this specimen in our two-gene analysis may be artificially high due to the absence of RAG 
<number box="[1427,1436,727,751]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.0">1</number>
sequence (Table 
<number box="[337,353,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2.0">2</number>
), the&gt; 
<number box="[430,459,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="20.0">20</number>
% ND 
<number box="[529,542,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="2.0">2</number>
divergence from typical 
<taxonomicName box="[820,902,762,787]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Afroedura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="halli">
<emphasis box="[820,902,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="471">A. halli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which vary among themselves by 
<number box="[1294,1411,763,787]" pageId="20" pageNumber="471" value="1.61" valueMax="3.02" valueMin="0.2">0.20–3.02</number>
%, supports the view that this represents a different species.
</paragraph>
